WEBVTT

00:00.300 --> 00:03.934
Quorum — the Nonprofit Board OS.

00:04.234 --> 00:11.732
Your Dashboard is the front page of your foundation's launch. Let's read it together,
from the top.

00:12.032 --> 00:24.906
First, the greeting — the portal knows who you are. And in the top corner sits the
launch progress ring: eight of twenty-seven tasks done so far. It fills in as you go.

00:25.206 --> 00:35.800
Under the greeting are four small cards. Awaiting signature counts documents waiting in
DocuSeal. Signed shows what's completed and filed.

00:36.100 --> 00:44.510
Open tasks is what's left on your launch checklist. And Next meeting shows the very next
date on the board's calendar.

00:44.810 --> 00:54.324
The Launch checklist card previews your next few steps. Clicking View all takes you to
the full roadmap — we'll tour it in the next video.

00:54.624 --> 01:05.770
Below that, Recent documents. Each one wears a little badge — Draft, Awaiting
signatures, or Fully signed — so you can spot what needs attention.

01:06.070 --> 01:15.104
On the right: Upcoming meetings. When a meeting has a video call, there's a blue Join
button — one click, and you're in.

01:15.404 --> 01:23.622
And the top bar works everywhere. Search your documents on the left... or jot something
down with New note on the right.

01:23.922 --> 01:35.404
That's your Dashboard — mission control. When in doubt, come back here: it always shows
what needs you next. Next up: the Launch Checklist.
